│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1.          │
│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs due to an assertion in             │
│ ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps that requires dependency information   │
│ to be valid before modifying UnscheduledDeps. The scheduling code sometimes   │
│ decrements control dependencies even when their dependency info has not been  │
│ initialized, leading to this assertion failure.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's         │
│ Log:\nThe debug log shows multiple scheduling attempts, including handling of │
│ control dependencies for a call instruction (%call12). The crash is triggered │
│ while processing control dependencies:\n  SLP:   check for readiness (ctrl):  │
│ %call12 = tail call i32 @fn1(i32 %add)\nImmediately after that, schedule()    │
│ tries to decrement dependencies via DecrUnsched with IsControl=true, even if  │
│ dependency info for the control-dependent node is not yet valid.\nThe key     │
│ code path:\n- BlockScheduling::schedule() creates lambda DecrUnsched that     │
│ calls Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) if (IsControl ||                     │
│ Data->hasValidDependencies()).\n- However, incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts   │
│ hasValidDependencies(), regardless of IsControl. Thus, calling                │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps when IsControl==true but                             │
│ hasValidDependencies()==false violates the assertion.\n\n3. Root Cause        │
│ Analysis:\nIn DecrUnsched, the condition allows decrement for control         │
│ dependencies without ensuring the dependency counters are initialized. Yet,   │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps requires valid Dependencies state. This mismatch     │
│ causes the assertion when encountering control dependencies whose dependency  │
│ info was not yet calculated (Dependencies == InvalidDeps).\nControl           │
│ dependencies are added via addControlDependency, but their dep counters may   │
│ not have been initialized. When a bundle member is scheduled and its control  │
│ dependencies are processed, DecrUnsched is invoked with IsControl=true. If    │
│ the control dependency ScheduleData still has Dependencies==InvalidDeps,      │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit file    │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp, inside                       │
│ BlockScheduling::schedule() around the DecrUnsched lambda (lines ~5405-5439). │
│ Before calling incrementUnscheduledDeps for control dependencies, ensure the  │
│ dependency counters are initialized. A minimal and safe fix is to initialize  │
│ a single dependency for control deps when their dependency information is     │
│ invalid. This models the scheduling dependency from the current instruction   │
│ to the control-dependent one and allows a single decrement to transition to   │
│ ready state.\n\nSuggested change:\nIn the DecrUnsched lambda, insert:\n  if   │
│ (IsControl && !Data->hasValidDependencies()) {\n    // Initialize a single    │
│ dependency for control-dependent nodes so that\n    // a single decrement     │
│ makes them ready.\n    Data->initDependencies();\n                            │
│ Data->incDependencies();\n    Data->resetUnscheduledDeps();\n  }\nThen        │
│ proceed with incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) as before.\n\nThis preserves the    │
│ current control-dependency semantics used by the scheduler and avoids         │
│ violating the assertion.\n\nEdit point specification:\n- File:                │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n- Lines: 5405-5439 (the body │
│ of the DecrUnsched lambda)\n- Change: Add initialization for control          │
│ dependencies if invalid before calling incrementUnscheduledDeps.\n\n5.        │
│ Conclusion:\nThe crash is due to decrementing control dependencies without    │
│ initializing dependency counters, violating the assert in                     │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps. Initializing a single dependency for                │
│ control-dependent nodes when their dependencies are invalid ensures that      │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps can safely be called and that the control-dependent  │
│ node can become ready after one decrement. This fix aligns with the           │
