│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion in                                       │
│ ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps that requires dependency information   │
│ to be valid before modifying UnscheduledDeps. The scheduling code sometimes   │
│ decrements control dependencies even when their dependency info has not been  │
│ initialized, leading to this assertion failure.                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug log shows multiple scheduling attempts, including handling of       │
│ control dependencies for a call instruction (%call12). The crash is triggered │
│ while processing control dependencies:                                        │
│   SLP:   check for readiness (ctrl): %call12 = tail call i32 @fn1(i32 %add)   │
│ Immediately after that, schedule() tries to decrement dependencies via        │
│ DecrUnsched with IsControl=true, even if dependency info for the              │
│ control-dependent node is not yet valid.                                      │
│ The key code path:                                                            │
│ - BlockScheduling::schedule() creates lambda DecrUnsched that calls           │
│ Data->incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) if (IsControl ||                           │
│ Data->hasValidDependencies()).                                                │
│ - However, incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts hasValidDependencies(),           │
│ regardless of IsControl. Thus, calling incrementUnscheduledDeps when          │
│ IsControl==true but hasValidDependencies()==false violates the assertion.     │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ In DecrUnsched, the condition allows decrement for control dependencies       │
│ without ensuring the dependency counters are initialized. Yet,                │
│ incrementUnscheduledDeps requires valid Dependencies state. This mismatch     │
│ causes the assertion when encountering control dependencies whose dependency  │
│ info was not yet calculated (Dependencies == InvalidDeps).                    │
│ Control dependencies are added via addControlDependency, but their dep        │
│ counters may not have been initialized. When a bundle member is scheduled and │
│ its control dependencies are processed, DecrUnsched is invoked with           │
│ IsControl=true. If the control dependency ScheduleData still has              │
│ Dependencies==InvalidDeps, incrementUnscheduledDeps asserts.                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit file llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp, inside             │
│ BlockScheduling::schedule() around the DecrUnsched lambda (lines ~5405-5439). │
│ Before calling incrementUnscheduledDeps for control dependencies, ensure the  │
│ dependency counters are initialized. A minimal and safe fix is to initialize  │
│ a single dependency for control deps when their dependency information is     │
│ invalid. This models the scheduling dependency from the current instruction   │
│ to the control-dependent one and allows a single decrement to transition to   │
│ ready state.                                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ Suggested change:                                                             │
│ In the DecrUnsched lambda, insert:                                            │
│   if (IsControl && !Data->hasValidDependencies()) {                           │
│     // Initialize a single dependency for control-dependent nodes so that     │
│     // a single decrement makes them ready.                                   │
│     Data->initDependencies();                                                 │
│     Data->incDependencies();                                                  │
│     Data->resetUnscheduledDeps();                                             │
│   }                                                                           │
│ Then proceed with incrementUnscheduledDeps(-1) as before.                     │
│                                                                               │
│ This preserves the current control-dependency semantics used by the scheduler │
│ and avoids violating the assertion.                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit point specification:                                                     │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                       │
│ - Lines: 5405-5439 (the body of the DecrUnsched lambda)                       │
│ - Change: Add initialization for control dependencies if invalid before       │
│ calling incrementUnscheduledDeps.                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is due to decrementing control dependencies without initializing    │
│ dependency counters, violating the assert in incrementUnscheduledDeps.        │
│ Initializing a single dependency for control-dependent nodes when their       │
│ dependencies are invalid ensures that incrementUnscheduledDeps can safely be  │
│ called and that the control-dependent node can become ready after one         │
│ decrement. This fix aligns with the scheduler's intent and prevents the abort │
│ in the provided reproducer.                                                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
